FBIS4-39172 "drsov108_f_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-108 Daily Report 4 Jun 1994 National Affairs CSCE Commissioner on Crimea CSCE Commissioner on Crimea LD0406145694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1435 GMT 4 Jun 94 LD0406145694 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Report by UKRINFORM correspondent Alexey Trotsenko] [Text] Kiev, 4 June (TASS) -- A major principle of CSCE is inviolability of borders; this principle should be the basic one in the search for mutually acceptable solutions of Ukrainian-Crimean problems, CSCE High Commissioner for Ethnic Minorities Max Van der Stoel said here today. The high commissioner has been to Ukraine on a four-day visit to meet Ukrainian and Crimean officials and discuss the situation around the Crimea. In his words, CSCE will render comprehensive assistance to the settlement of Ukrainian-Crimean problems on the basis of inviolability of borders.
